---
!!!<p><span class="yellow-status">in progress</span></p>
---
* âœ… `print` - A `print` function will be introduced instead of `print` statement.
* âœ… `println` - A `print` function that suffix a new line character.
* âœ… `len` - Get length of strings and other data structures provided by the language.
* âŒ `sizeof` - Size of structures or C data types.
* âŒ `tostr` - If it is a string, copy is created. Floats are converted to 2 decimal places. 
* âœ… `arrput` - Put item to an array.
* âœ… `arrpop` - Remove last item from an array and return it.
* âœ… `getref` - Get a pointer to given object.
* âœ… `unref` - Dereference a pointer.
* âœ… `charat` - Get a character at a specific location in string.
* âœ… `shnew` - Initialize `Array[SMEntry[T]]` object .
* âœ… `shput` - Put item to a `Array[SMEntry[T]]`.
* âœ… `shget` - Get item from a `Array[SMEntry[T]]`.
* âœ… `shgeti` - Get item index from a `Array[SMEntry[T]]` (-1 if not found).
* âœ… `hmnew` - Initialize `Array[MEntry[T]]` object.
* âœ… `hmput` - Put item to a `Array[MEntry[T]]`.
* âœ… `hmget` - Get item from a `Array[MEntry[T]]`.
* âœ… `hmgeti` - Get item index from a `Array[MEntry[T]]` (-1 if not found).
* âŒ `reversed` - Reverse an array creating a new array. New array need to be deleted.
* âŒ `sorted` - Sort an array creating a new array. New array need to be deleted.
